âœ… C. Chat Ban â€” Final Notes (CP Revision)
ğŸ¯ Problem
link: https://codeforces.com/problemset/problem/1612/C
You want to send messages in this pattern of emotes:

1, 2, 3, ..., k-1, k, k-1, ..., 2, 1   â†’ total 2kâˆ’1 messages


Auto-mod bans you as soon as total emotes â‰¥ x.

Task:
Find how many messages you send before getting banned.
If you finish all 2kâˆ’1 messages without reaching x, answer = 2kâˆ’1.

ğŸ§  Observation
Sum of first m natural numbers:
sum(m) = m*(m+1)/2

For first k messages:
1 + 2 + ... + k = sum(k)

Total emotes in whole triangle:
Total = sum(k) + sum(k-1)


If x > Total â†’ you never get banned â†’ answer = 2kâˆ’1.

ğŸ“Œ Prefix Sum Behavior

Prefix messages:

If mid â‰¤ k (ascending phase):

cnt = sum(mid)


If mid > k (descending phase):

cnt = sum(k) + sum(kâˆ’1) âˆ’ sum(2kâˆ’1âˆ’mid)


We need smallest mid such that:

cnt â‰¥ x


This is binary search on messages.

âœ… Algorithm

Let low = 1, high = 2kâˆ’1

Binary search for earliest mid where prefix sum â‰¥ x

If none found â†’ answer = 2kâˆ’1

âš™ï¸ Time Complexity
O(log k) per test case


Perfect for large k (â‰¤ 1e9)

âœ… Final Code (C++ Recommended)
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
using ll = long long;

ll sum(ll n) {
    return n * (n + 1) / 2;
}

void solve() {
    ll k, x;
    cin >> k >> x;

    ll total = sum(k) + sum(k - 1);
    if (x > total) {
        cout << 2 * k - 1 << "\n";
        return;
    }

    ll low = 1, high = 2 * k - 1, ans = 2 * k - 1;

    while (low <= high) {
        ll mid = (low + high) / 2;
        ll cnt;

        if (mid <= k) {
            cnt = sum(mid);
        } else {
            cnt = sum(k) + sum(k - 1) - sum(2 * k - 1 - mid);
        }

        if (cnt >= x) {
            ans = mid;
            high = mid - 1;
        } else {
            low = mid + 1;
        }
    }

    cout << ans << "\n";
}

int main() {
    ios::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(nullptr);

    int t;
    cin >> t;
    while (t--) solve();
}

ğŸ“ Mini Example
Input:
k = 4, x = 7


Messages: 1 2 3 4 3 2 1
Prefix sums: 1 3 6 10 ...

At 4th message sum = 10 â‰¥ 7 â†’ banned
Output = 4

ğŸ’¡ Key Points

Triangle total = sum(k) + sum(kâˆ’1)

If x is bigger â†’ finish all messages

Otherwise, binary search first time prefix â‰¥ x

Use formula, no loops over messages
